### Root Cause Analysis

The issue labeled "E2E: Maestro Device Testing - Basic App Flow Validation" likely stems from inconsistencies or errors in the React Native application that cause it to fail basic flow validations during end-to-end (E2E) testing with Maestro. Possible causes include:
- **Code Non-Conformance:** The code may not adhere to React Native standards, leading to issues like inline styles and unused imports.
- **Dependency Issues:** Missing or incorrect dependencies in `useEffect` might cause unexpected behavior.
- **Unused Imports/Variables:** Unnecessary imports or variables can bloat the bundle and lead to runtime issues.
- **Color Literals:** Direct usage of color literals instead of theme constants can result in style inconsistencies.

### Code Solution

Below is a sample React Native component demonstrating best practices and adhering to the coding standards provided. This example focuses on a generic screen that might be part of the app's basic flow:

```javascript
// Import order: React, third-party, local
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import theme from '../theme'; // Local import for theme constants

const HomeScreen = () => {
  const fetchData = async () => {
    // Mock API call
    return await fetch('https://api.example.com/data').then((res) => res.json());
  };

  // Correctly using useQuery and including dependencies in useEffect
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery(['data'], fetchData);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (error) {
      console.error('Error fetching data:', error);
    }
  }, [error]); // All dependencies included

  if (isLoading) return <Text>Loading...</Text>;
  if (error) return <Text>Error: {error.message}</Text>;

  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <Text style={styles.title}>Welcome to MapYourHealth</Text>
      {data && <Text>{JSON.stringify(data)}</Text>}
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    padding: 10,
    backgroundColor: theme.backgroundColor, // Using theme constant
  },
  title: {
    fontSize: 24,
    color: theme.textColor, // Using theme constant
    marginBottom: 20,
  },
});

export default HomeScreen;
```

